[For discussion of scrub typhus, see moderator's comments in prior ProMED-mail posts.

The southern Indian state of Kerala on the Malabar Coast of the Arabian Sea is divided into 14 districts. Kozhikode District is in the northwest; the city of Kozhikode, also known as Calicut, is the district headquarters, with a metropolitan population of 2 030 519 in 2011 (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kozhikode). Wayanad is a district of which only 3.79 percent is urbanized, to the east of Kozhikode District (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wayanad_district). - Mod.ML

